<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-31T20:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-31T20:34:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/8674: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Acting President of the Technical Board</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-01T10:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">June 1,
                                        1921—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 3—1:14
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>… Negotiations in progress between the Chita government and the Kappel
                            leaders which [<hi rend="italic">will?</hi>] undoubtedly lead to
                            understanding thus eliminating Semenoff.</p>
                        <p>Referring to my cable of May 13, 4 p.m.,<note n="32" xml:id="d674fn32">Not printed.</note> no particular change in the Chinese Eastern
                            situation. Export movement continues unmolested via Vladivostok.
                            Persistent rumors here that Japanese banks prepared to advance two and a
                            half million yen to the Chinese Eastern about June 10, presumably on
                            arrangement with the Chinese Minister of Finance. No details as to
                            terms.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>